    "id": "s2",
    "n_params": 0,
    "step_txt": "\nFor the first problem, lets consider the left hand side of the equation.\n\\[\n\t\\textrm{LHS } = \\frac{w + x }{y + z }\n\\]\n\\[\n\t= \\frac{kx + x }{kz + z }\n\\]"
  }, {
    "id": "s3",
    "n_params": 0,
    "step_txt": "\n\\[\n\t= \\frac{x (k + 1)}{z (k + 1)} = \\frac{x }{z }\n\\]"
  }, {
    "id": "s4",
    "n_params": 0,
    "step_txt": "\nNow lets consider the right hand side of the equation\n\\[\n\t\\textrm{RHS } = \\frac{\\sqrt{2 w ^2 + 7 x ^2 }}{\\sqrt{2 y ^2 + 7 z ^2}}\n\\]\n\\[\n\t= \\frac{\\sqrt{2 k ^2 x ^2 + 7 x ^2 }}{\\sqrt{2 k ^2 z ^2 + 7 z ^2}}\n\\]"
  }, {
    "id": "s5",
    "n_params": 0,
    "step_txt": "\n\\[\n\t= \\frac{\\sqrt{x ^2 (2 k ^2 + 7)}}{\\sqrt{z ^2 (2 k ^2 + 7)}}\n\\]\n\\[\n\t=\\frac{x }{z }\n\\]"
  }, {
    "id": "s6",
    "n_params": 0,
    "step_txt": "$$\\text{From the above expressions we can say that LHS $=$ RHS for the first equation.\nNow, for the second equation, lets consider the left hand side of the equation.}$$\n\\[\n\t\\textrm{LHS } = \\frac{\\sqrt{w ^4 + y ^4 }}{\\sqrt{x ^4 + z ^4 }}\n\\]\n\\[\n\t= \\frac{\\sqrt{k ^4 x ^4 + k ^4 z ^4 }}{\\sqrt{x ^4 + z ^4}}\n\\]"
  }, {
    "id": "s7",
    "n_params": 0,
    "step_txt": "\n\\[\n\t= \\frac{\\sqrt{k ^4 (x ^4 + z ^4)}}{\\sqrt{x ^4 + z ^4}}\n\\]\n\\[\n\t= \\sqrt{k ^4} = k ^2 \n\\]"
  }, {
    "id": "s8",
    "n_params": 0,
    "step_txt": "\nNow, right hand side of the equation can be written as\n\\[\n\t\\textrm{RHS } = \\frac{m w ^2 + n y ^2 }{m x ^2 + n z ^2 }\n\\]\n\\[\n\t= \\frac{m k ^2 x ^2 + n k ^2 z ^2}{m x ^2 + n z ^2}\n\\]"
  }, {
    "id": "s9",
    "n_params": 0,
    "step_txt": "\n\\[\n\t= \\frac{k ^2 (m x ^2 + n z ^2)}{m x ^2 + n z ^2}\n\\]\n\\[\n\t= k ^2\n\\]"
  }, {
    "id": "s10",
    "n_params": 0,
    "step_txt": "$$\\text{\nNow, from the above two expressions we can write that LHS $=$ RHS. \n\nHence proved.\n\\newline\n}$$\n"
  }]
};
